  <compounddef id="SPRITECOLLIDE" kind="page">
    <compoundname>SPRITECOLLIDE</compoundname>
    <title>SPRITECOLLIDE Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>SPRITECOLLIDE(sprite_a, ax, ay, sprite_b, bx, by)</para>
<para>Checks whether two sprites collide using pixel-perfect collision detection.</para>
<para>Returns TRUE if any opaque pixels overlap, or FALSE if they do not.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para>Examples</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Simple<sp/>collision<sp/>check</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">IF<sp/>SPRITECOLLIDE(player,<sp/>px,<sp/>py,<sp/>enemy,<sp/>ex,<sp/>ey)<sp/>THEN</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>PRINT<sp/>&quot;Hit!&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">ENDIF</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Bullet<sp/>collision</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">FOR<sp/>i<sp/>=<sp/>0<sp/>TO<sp/>bullet_count<sp/>-<sp/>1</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>IF<sp/>SPRITECOLLIDE(bullet(i),<sp/>bx(i),<sp/>by(i),<sp/>enemy,<sp/>ex,<sp/>ey)<sp/>THEN</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>PRINT<sp/>&quot;Enemy<sp/>hit&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>ENDIF</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">NEXT</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para>Notes</para>
<para>Uses sprite transparency for collision.</para>
<para>Sprites must be loaded with <ref refid="SPRITELOAD" kindref="compound">SPRITELOAD</ref>.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para>See also: <ref refid="SPRITELOAD" kindref="compound">SPRITELOAD</ref> · <ref refid="PLOT" kindref="compound">PLOT</ref> · <ref refid="ANIMATE" kindref="compound">ANIMATE</ref> </para>
